        <p>
          Recall the relabeling method in <xref ref="exercise_GroupActions_Conj3">Exercise</xref>.
          We recommend using this method to save time when making conjugacy tables.
        </p>
        <p>
          For instance,
          to simplify <m>(12)\compose (23)\compose (12)</m> we can relabel (23) according to (12).
          That is: <m>2\rightarrow 1</m> and <m>3\rightarrow 3</m>.
          So, <m>(12)\compose (23)\compose (12)=(13)</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </example>
    <p>
      In the next exercise you may practice creating a conjugacy table using both permutation notation and the relabeling method.
    </p>
